     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="18"/>
   <head>M<seg rend="sup">r</seg>. <hi>William Allison,</hi> Minister of the Word at <hi>Norwich.</hi>
   </head>
   <l>REader, see here, (if thou canst rightly looke)</l>
   <l>More in this Title, than in many a booke:</l>
   <l>Man's all: Death's more, Deuotion only can</l>
   <l>Sweeten the harsh Death of a Dying man.</l>
   <l>Death it kills Man: Deuotion Death corrects,</l>
   <l>As here thou seest by manifold Collects:</l>
   <l>Therefore peruse it, I dare boldly say,</l>
   <l>A Golden head ne're had a Corps of clay.</l>
</div>
